articles.content:
The Agency is funded by:
1. Budgets approved and allocated by the government and donations (subsidies) from the government;
2. Donations from domestic and overseas public or private institutions, groups, or individuals;
3. Income from the research entrusted to the Agency and the services provided by the Agency;
4. Income from operations and research accomplishments; and
5. Other income.
The donations specified in Subparagraph 2 of the preceding Paragraph are regarded as the donations to the government.
